Here's the full program:

```csharp
using System.Text.Json;

var person = new Person("Alice", 30);

var options = new JsonSerializerOptions
{
    PropertyNamingPolicy = JsonNamingPolicy.PascalCase,
    WriteIndented = true
};

Console.WriteLine(JsonSerializer.Serialize(person, options));

public record Person(string name, int age);
```

**Output:**
```json
{
  "Name": "Alice",
  "Age": 30
}
```

.NET 11 added the built-in `JsonNamingPolicy.PascalCase` policy, so no custom class is needed. It converts the lowercase record parameter names (`name`, `age`) to PascalCase (`Name`, `Age`) in the JSON output.
